translation.text: Blue Mountains Line, Western Line - Delays

Delays are continuing to effect services from the city due to signal equipment repairs at Granville. Please listen to local announcements, check information screens and transport apps and allow for an additional travel time of up to 20 minutes.

Trains are suspended between Lidcombe and Regents Park due to overhead power supply repairs at Regents Park. Buses are operating as a replacement service between Bankstown and Lidcombe until train services can resume. Customers are also advised to utilise local bus routes. Major delays and additional travel time expected. A reduced frequency train service will operate for customers travelling to Yagoona and Birrong. This service disruption is expected to continue into this evening.
Special Events - A-League Western Sydney Warriors V Melbourne Victory - Bankwest Stadium Parramatta

Wednesday 10 February

- The closest station to Bankwest Stadium is Parramatta. The stadium is approximately 15 minutes walk from the station exiting via Darcy St then continuing on Church St, the Riverside Walk (non-accessible route) or through Prince Alfred Square to the stadium on O'Connell St.

For more information visit https://transportnsw.info/events/2021/02

Station Update - Berala, Lidcombe, Regents Park

Due to overhead power supply repairs at Regents Park, trains are suspended between Lidcombe and Regents Park. Buses are operating as a replacement service between Bankstown and Lidcombe until train services can resume. Customers can also utilise local bus routes. Major delays and additional travel time expected. This service disruption is expected to continue into this evening.

Due to overhead power supply repairs at Regents Park, a reduced frequency service is currently operating. Buses are operating between Bankstown and Lidcombe. Major delays and added travel time expected. This service disruption is expected to continue into this evening.

From 11 January to end-December 2021, the escalators and staircase connecting the corner of Pitt Street and Eddy Avenue with the Grand Concourse and L1 Light Rail stop will be closed due to station upgrade works. 

To access the Grand Concourse and Platforms 1  12 from the street level, please use the Western Forecourt entry via Pitt Street. To access Platforms 16  25 from the street level, please use the Eddy Avenue entry. 

To access Pitt Street or Eddy Avenue from the Grand Concourse or L1 light rail stop, please exit the station via the Western Forecourt or Northern Concourse.

There are changes happening at Central Station due to Sydney Metro construction works. Access to certain areas of the station and platforms may mean using different stairs, escalators and lifts. Please follow the signs and staff directions. If you need assistance, see station staff. For detailed information please visit https://transportnsw.info/alerts/details#/6049959
Due to station redevelopment work some platforms have reduced capacity. Please avoid standing in front of construction zones and remain behind the yellow line on the platform

Platforms 4, 5 & 6 upgrade works. A new Metro concourse is being constructed on the northern end of Sydenham Station. While the concourse is being installed, please board and alight from the first 5 carriages of the train on platforms 4 & 6 and the last 6 carriages of the train on platform 5. If you need help, please ask staff at the station. For more information on these upgrades, please see sydneymetro.info
